post_text: Hey radio play fans...Auditions for the fall radio play, War of the Worlds: The Panic Broadcast by Joe Landry will occur on Sept. 15th-17th. Voices and sound/video editors needed for this unique approach to a radio play / podcast. Grades 4-12 are welcome to audition. Auditions are in half-hour slots with 12 people per section. Please sign up for a section in the office. Rehearsals will be limited and the performance will be recorded and streamed over Halloween weekend. Please contact Mr. Musselman if you have any further questions or concerns.

Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.
Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

Please click on the link below to see the latest info on our summer programs!

Rescheduled: Sole Sisters:
Sole Sisters is a fun program for 3-8th grade girls that will promote lifelong health and fitness while encouraging emotional, social, mental, and physical development. Half the program will focus on fitness with a variety of activities and games. The other half of the program will teach girls the importance of relationships, teamwork, healthy eating, and building each other up.

Rescheduled: Horse Appreciation II&III: Like horses? Spend five days learning about this incredible equine companion. Learn proper feeding, tack, attire, safety, and riding!

NEW: Softball Skills Camp: Come join us and improve your softball game and learn basic skills of softball: hitting, fielding, pitching, catching, base running, teamwork, offensive and defensive strategies.

post_text: The fourth graders were unable to go on their field trip to Mystery Cave. BUT that didn’t stop them from learning about caves! All week students built their own caves, as well as learned about cave creatures, cave formations, and cave paintings. Students then recreated these items and incorporated them into their caves. At the end of the week they had to advertise for their caves, and let’s just say the 4th grade teachers were very impressed with the creativity of these fourth grade students! Distance learning wasn’t planned but the fourth graders are sure making the most of it! - The 4th Grade Team

post_text: 🍎Congratulations to Mr. Duane Koenen, our May APPLE AWARD recipient! The Apple Award (A Positive Person Leads Everyone) is given to one staff member a month who is nominated by their peers. Duane is a humble and quiet leader throughout our school and community. He has dedicated his whole career to the students here at RP. He is a great teacher, a truly great role model to students and other staff, and he has definitely made a difference here at RP inside the classroom and out over his career. Duane’s expectations and work ethic should be emulated by all staff here at RP! We appreciate you Duane and all you've given of yourself to better the lives of our youth. Much deserved!

post_text: Congratulations to Hans Lind on being recruited and accepting a judging scholarship to Fort Scott Community College in Fort Scott, KS. At Fort Scott, Hans will be a member of the Livestock Evaluation Program. Hans was recruited by Fort Scott based of his success and judging skills displayed during his high school career. His scholarship covers the full cost of tuition and living expenses. The livestock judging team travels across the country and competes at numerous contests from Austin, MN to Houston Texas, and California to the east coast.

post_text:
Rushford-Peterson Schools will be joining #BeTheLightMN and will be turning on the lights on our football and baseball fields as well as in the gym as a beacon of hope for our students!

These facilities will be lit up in honor of all of our students every Friday night from 8:20-8:40pm. While we are certainly missing all of our students, we understand that this is an especially difficult time for our seniors. With this light, we honor our seniors. Please practice social distancing and enjoy the lights from afar! Go Trojans!!

post_text:
Hey, Hey... It's Paraprofessional Appreciation Day!!

We want to take this opportunity and thank our wonderful paraprofessionals at Rushford-Peterson! The dedication and hard work these individuals put in each and every day with our students and staff does NOT go unnoticed. It's unfortunate we aren't all together to honor you in a more proper way...

Thanks for ALL you do! Our school is better because of each one of you. The relationships you build with students is top notch and we can't thank you enough!

Thank you for your extra time, efforts and dedication to staff and students during "Distance Learning". You have made child care, cleaning, daily lunches, distance learning run smoothly!

Please help us in thanking our team of paraprofessionals for the job they do.

Please refrain from posting any and all login information for your child's device online. Those logins are class-specific and are meant only for your students' classroom. Security of data and privacy for your students is tops on our list!!

Also, if there are any concerns about device availability for your student, or questions about login information, contact your student's teacher directly or contact Mr. Mattson for information as well.

Thank you!!

Offer below from AcenTek to families of K-12 and college age students who do not have internet access:

AcenTek Keeps You Connected During Shutdown
As our country comes together to make decisions to help prevent the spread of the coronavirus, AcenTek understands that your connection to the internet is more important than ever.

With the state-recommended school closings in mind, AcenTek will offer free broadband and WiFi internet access until June 1, 2020, to students and teachers who do not currently have internet service with us. Installation fees will also be waived for the new customers living within the service area. Students (K-12/college) and teachers facing the effects of the shutdown, will now have access to free internet to learn, work and communicate remotely. Contact our office at 888.404.4940 to sign up.

At this time, it has been decided to delay the start of the 7th & 8th grade softball and baseball seasons. This has not been an easy decision, but it is the step that will be taken. We are cautiously optomistic that both programs will begin when school resumes in a few weeks. These are important programs and this decision was not made lightly.

High school baseball and softball will have practice on Monday & Tuesday. Both teams will practice after school--which is a change for the baseball team.

Thank you for your understanding and support,

RP Softball & Baseball programs
